AlgorithmParameterSpec
public class LunaParameterSpecOAEP
extends Object
implements AlgorithmParameterSpec

A parameter spec for OAEP parameters There is actually very little flexibility in the OAEP parameter specification. The hash algorithm must be SHA1, the mask generation function must be MGF1 and the source type must be DATA_SPECIFIED. Nonetheless, all of these fields must be specified with the generic constructor.

LunaParameterSpecOAEP

public LunaParameterSpecOAEP()
Default constructor for a LunaParameterSpecOAEP object. The hash algorithm, mask function and data source are set to SHA1, MGF1 and DATA_SPECIFIED respectively. The source data is empty.

Generic constructor for a LunaParameterOAEP object.

Parameters:

sourceType - The source type to use (must be sourceType_DATA_SPECIFIED)
